<p>Choosing the right words during this sensitive period is essential.  A carefully crafted message, reflecting genuine sorrow and heartfelt support, can provide comfort and strengthen bonds. Avoid overly formal language; sincerity and empathy should be the guiding principles.  Remember to personalize your message, referencing a cherished memory or shared experience to deepen its impact.  Always maintain a respectful and comforting tone, acknowledging the pain without minimizing their loss.</p>
    

